Path: godot/classes/class_navigationobstacle3d.rst
Summary: Lists the properties available for the NavigationObstacle3D class, detailing their types, names, and default values.

Properties
* affect_navigation_mesh (bool): If `true`, the obstacle will affect the navigation mesh. Default: `false`.
* avoidance_enabled (bool): If `true`, the obstacle will be considered by the avoidance system. Default: `true`.
* avoidance_layers (int): The avoidance layers this obstacle belongs to. Default: `1`.
* carve_navigation_mesh (bool): If `true`, the obstacle will carve a hole in the navigation mesh. Default: `false`.
* height (float): The height of the obstacle when carving the navigation mesh. Default: `1.0`.
* radius (float): The radius of the obstacle when carving the navigation mesh. Default: `0.0`.
* use_3d_avoidance (bool): If `true`, the obstacle will use 3D avoidance. Default: `false`.
* velocity (Vector3): The current velocity of the obstacle. Default: `Vector3(0, 0, 0)`.
* vertices (PackedVector3Array): The vertices of the obstacle when carving the navigation mesh. Default: `PackedVector3Array()`.
---CHUNK---
